decks.notes: This Esper Control deck focuses on using powerful spells and disruptive creatures to control the game and outmaneuver opponents. It utilizes a combination of card draw, counterspells, removal, and disruptive creatures like Lavinia, Azorius Renegade to disrupt opponents' game plans. The deck also includes Mishra's Bauble and Psychic Frog for additional card advantage and disruption. With a strong mana base and access to powerful cards like Ancestral Recall and Timetwister, the deck aims to control the game until it can secure a win condition and pull ahead.

The main concept of this deck is to quickly fill the graveyard with creatures using cards like Bazaar of Baghdad and Golgari Thug, and then use cards like Creeping Chill and Prized Amalgam to quickly overwhelm the opponent with powerful creatures coming back from the graveyard. The deck also includes disruption with cards like Cabal Therapy and Force of Will, as well as protection with Force of Negation. The ultimate goal is to assemble a board presence that is difficult for the opponent to deal with, leading to a quick victory through explosive combo plays.

The deck revolves around using various reanimation spells to bring powerful creatures back from the graveyard, such as Grief and Troll of Khazad-dûm. It also includes disruption and control elements like Force of Will and Null Rod to protect the combo and disrupt the opponent's strategy. The deck aims to quickly assemble its combo pieces and overwhelm the opponent with powerful threats, all while controlling the game with counterspells and disruption. The key strategy is to efficiently reanimate creatures and disrupt the opponent's game plan to secure victory.

The primary focus of this deck is to control the game through a combination of countering spells, disrupting the opponent's strategy, and generating card advantage. The deck utilizes powerful control elements such as Force of Will, Swords to Plowshares, and Lórien Revealed to stay ahead in the game. The inclusion of card draw spells like Ancestral Recall and Dig Through Time helps ensure consistent access to resources, while disruptive cards like Strip Mine and Wasteland can slow down the opponent's mana development. With a strong control game plan, this deck aims to outlast opponents and secure victory through strategic decision-making.

This Vintage Aggro MUD deck focuses on using artifact mana acceleration and disruptive artifacts like Chalice of the Void, Sphere of Resistance, and Trinisphere to slow down the opponent's game plan. The deck also utilizes Mishra's Workshop and Ancient Tomb to power out threats like Phyrexian Metamorph, Lodestone Golem, and Golos, Tireless Pilgrim. The deck aims to disrupt the opponent's strategy while presenting a fast clock with efficient threats like Arcbound Ravager and Mishra's Factory. Karn, the Great Creator provides additional utility and answers to problematic artifacts.

The deck focuses on generating card advantage and aggression by using Bazaar of Baghdad to quickly fill the graveyard with creatures like Vengevine and Squee, Goblin Nabob. By utilizing cards like Force of Will and Force of Negation to protect key pieces and disrupt opponents, it aims to overwhelm the opponent with powerful threats like Hollow One and Master of Death early in the game. The deck also includes disruptive elements like Chalice of the Void and Wasteland to control the board and prevent the opponent from mounting a defense.
